  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div xml:id="AN127.2-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">piriviṭaiyāṟṟāḷākiya talaimakaḷait tōḻi vaṟpuṟuttiyatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">How the confidante encouraged HER who did not have the strength in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
        <div xml:id="AN127.2">
            <lg type="edition">
                <l>ilaṅkuvaḷai ñekiḻac cāa yalkaluṅ</l>
                <l>kalaṅkaña ruḻantu nāmiva ṇoḻiya</l>
                <l>valampaṭu muraciṟ cēra lātaṉ</l>
                <l>mu<supplied>nnī</supplied> rōṭṭik kaṭampeṟin timaiyattu</l>
                <l>muṉṉōr maruḷa vaṇaṅkuviṟ poṟittu</l>
                <l>naṉṉakar māntai muṟṟit toṉṉār</l>
                <l>paṇitiṟai tanta pāṭucā ṉaṉkalam</l>
                <l>poṉcey pāvai vayiramō ṭāmpa</l>
                <l>loṉṟuvāy niṟaiyak kuvaii yiyaṉṟava</l>
                <l>ṇilantiṉat tuṟanta nitiyat taṉṉa</l>
                <l>vorunā ḷorupakaṟ peṟiṉum vaḻināṭ</l>
                <l>ṭaṅkalar vāḻi tōḻi ceṅkōṟ</l>
                <l>karuṅkāṉ marāattu vāraṉ melliṇar</l>
                <l>curintuvaḷar pittai poliyac cūṭik</l>
                <l>kallā maḻavar villiṭan taḻīi</l>
                <l>varunarp pārkkum veruvaru kavalai</l>
                <l>moḻipeyar tēetta rāyiṉum</l>
                <l>paḻitīr kātalar ceṉṟa nāṭṭē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l>While we stay behind here, becoming emaciated so that</l>
                <l>[our] shining bangles come loose, bearing upsetting grief all night, (1f.)</l>
                <l>even if he were to obtain [wealth] one day, one midday (11)</l>
                <l>like the treasure that was abandoned, to be swallowed by the ground,</l>
                <l>there, after Cēralātaṉ, with a victory-bringing drum,</l>
                <l>had driven away the ocean, thrown down the Kadamba trees, engraved</l>
                <l>[his] bent bow [sign] on the Himālayas, so that the people of former times were awed,</l>
                <l>had finished off the good city of Māntai</l>
                <l>[and] in advancing heaped all in one place</l>
                <l>myriads of gold-made images along with diamonds,</l>
                <l>good ornaments worthy of song that were given as a humble tribute by the enemies, (3-10)</l>
                <l>he would not stay a day further, oh friend, (12)</l>
                <l>– in the land where [our] blame-less lover has gone, (17)</l>
                <l>even though it be [of] people from a country where the language differs,</l>
                <l>on frightening crossroads where uneducated warriors</l>
                <l>look out for [new]comers, clasping [their] bows on the left side,</l>
                <l>wearing, so that they shine in [their] curly growing hair tufts,</l>
                <l>dripping soft [flower] clusters from the black-trunked Kadamba tree  with red stems. (13-16)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
